      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Checking Context Fit Before Sending"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Always check that your messages fit inside the context window before sending. The Anthropic token counting API does this without invoking inference — it returns the exact input token count so you can compare against the model limit and adjust if needed."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "import anthropic\n\nclient = anthropic.Anthropic()\n\n# Context window limits per model\nCONTEXT_LIMITS = {\n    \"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001\": 200_000,\n    \"claude-sonnet-4-6\":          200_000,\n    # Check anthropic.com/docs for current values\n}\n\ndef fits_in_context(\n    messages: list[dict],\n    system: str,\n    model: str,\n    max_output_tokens: int,\n) -> tuple[bool, int, int]:\n    \"\"\"\n    Returns (fits, input_token_count, available_output_tokens).\n    \"\"\"\n    response = client.messages.count_tokens(\n        model=model,\n        system=system,\n        messages=messages,\n    )\n    input_tokens = response.input_tokens\n    limit = CONTEXT_LIMITS.get(model, 200_000)\n    available = limit - input_tokens\n    fits = available >= max_output_tokens\n    return fits, input_tokens, available\n\n# Example usage\nmessages = [{\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": \"Analyse the document: \" + \"word \" * 5000}]\nok, inp, avail = fits_in_context(\n    messages,\n    system=\"You are a document analyst.\",\n    model=\"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001\",\n    max_output_tokens=1024,\n)\nprint(f\"Fits: {ok}, input tokens: {inp}, available for output: {avail}\")\n# Fits: True, input tokens: 5025, available for output: 194975"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Strategies When Content Exceeds the Context Window"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "1. Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG)"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Instead of stuffing an entire document corpus into the context, embed each chunk, index them, and retrieve only the most relevant chunks at query time. The model sees a focused, dense context rather than a diluted long one — recall is better and costs are lower."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "from anthropic import Anthropic\n\nclient = Anthropic()\n\n# Simulated chunk retrieval (replace with vector DB lookup)\ndef retrieve_relevant_chunks(query: str, all_chunks: list[str], top_k: int = 3) -> list[str]:\n    \"\"\"In production: embed query + chunks, return top_k by cosine similarity.\"\"\"\n    # Simple keyword filter as placeholder\n    scored = [(chunk, sum(w in chunk.lower() for w in query.lower().split())) for chunk in all_chunks]\n    scored.sort(key=lambda x: x[1], reverse=True)\n    return [c for c, _ in scored[:top_k]]\n\ndef rag_answer(question: str, all_chunks: list[str]) -> str:\n    relevant = retrieve_relevant_chunks(question, all_chunks)\n    context = \"\\n\\n\".join(f\"[Chunk {i+1}]\\n{chunk}\" for i, chunk in enumerate(relevant))\n\n    response = client.messages.create(\n        model=\"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001\",\n        max_tokens=512,\n        system=\"Answer the question using only the provided context chunks. If the answer isn't in the context, say so.\",\n        messages=[\n            {\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": f\"Context:\\n{context}\\n\\nQuestion: {question}\"},\n        ],\n    )\n    return response.content[0].text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "2. Progressive Summarisation for Long Conversations"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "When a conversation history grows too long, summarise old turns rather than discarding them. This preserves semantic content at a fraction of the token cost, avoiding the hard cutoff that simple trimming introduces."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "from anthropic import Anthropic\n\nclient = Anthropic()\n\nSUMMARY_THRESHOLD = 8000   # token count at which we summarise old turns\nKEEP_RECENT_TURNS = 4      # always keep the most recent N turns verbatim\n\ndef summarise_old_turns(old_messages: list[dict]) -> str:\n    \"\"\"Compress old conversation turns into a compact summary.\"\"\"\n    transcript = \"\\n\".join(\n        f\"{m['role'].upper()}: {m['content']}\" for m in old_messages\n    )\n    response = client.messages.create(\n        model=\"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001\",\n        max_tokens=512,\n        system=\"Summarise the conversation history below in 3–5 bullet points. Preserve key facts, decisions, and user preferences.\",\n        messages=[{\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": transcript}],\n    )\n    return response.content[0].text\n\ndef compress_history(\n    messages: list[dict],\n    model: str = \"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001\",\n) -> list[dict]:\n    \"\"\"Compress history when approaching context limit.\"\"\"\n    token_response = client.messages.count_tokens(model=model, messages=messages)\n    if token_response.input_tokens < SUMMARY_THRESHOLD:\n        return messages  # no compression needed\n\n    split = max(0, len(messages) - KEEP_RECENT_TURNS * 2)\n    old = messages[:split]\n    recent = messages[split:]\n\n    if not old:\n        return messages  # nothing safe to summarise\n\n    summary_text = summarise_old_turns(old)\n    summary_message = {\n        \"role\": \"user\",\n        \"content\": f\"[Summary of earlier conversation]\\n{summary_text}\",\n    }\n    return [summary_message] + recent"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "3. Map-Reduce for Very Long Documents"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "When a document is too long to fit even a large context window, split it into chunks, process each independently (map), then combine the partial results (reduce). This avoids the lost-in-the-middle problem entirely by keeping each chunk comfortably sized."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "from anthropic import Anthropic\n\nclient = Anthropic()\n\ndef split_into_chunks(text: str, chunk_size: int = 3000) -> list[str]:\n    \"\"\"Split on word boundaries to chunk_size tokens (~4 chars/token estimate).\"\"\"\n    words = text.split()\n    approx_tokens_per_word = 1.3\n    words_per_chunk = int(chunk_size / approx_tokens_per_word)\n    return [\n        \" \".join(words[i : i + words_per_chunk])\n        for i in range(0, len(words), words_per_chunk)\n    ]\n\ndef map_reduce_summarise(document: str) -> str:\n    \"\"\"Summarise a document that exceeds a single context window.\"\"\"\n    chunks = split_into_chunks(document, chunk_size=3000)\n\n    # MAP: summarise each chunk independently\n    partial_summaries = []\n    for i, chunk in enumerate(chunks):\n        response = client.messages.create(\n            model=\"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001\",\n            max_tokens=256,\n            system=\"Summarise the following passage in 3–5 sentences.\",\n            messages=[{\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": chunk}],\n        )\n        partial_summaries.append(f\"[Part {i+1}]\\n{response.content[0].text}\")\n\n    # REDUCE: synthesise partial summaries into a final summary\n    combined = \"\\n\\n\".join(partial_summaries)\n    response = client.messages.create(\n        model=\"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001\",\n        max_tokens=512,\n        system=\"Synthesise the following partial summaries into a single coherent summary.\",\n        messages=[{\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": combined}],\n    )\n    return response.content[0].text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "4. Prompt Caching for Stable Long Contexts"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "If you are sending the same large document or system prompt on many requests (a knowledge base, a codebase, a product manual), Anthropic's prompt caching lets the server reuse the KV cache for that prefix. The full 200k-token document is only processed once; subsequent requests read it from cache at ~10% of the input token price."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "from anthropic import Anthropic\n\nclient = Anthropic()\n\nCODEBASE_CONTENT = \"...entire repository as text (150k tokens)...\"\n\ndef review_pr(pr_diff: str) -> str:\n    \"\"\"Each PR review reuses cached codebase context.\"\"\"\n    response = client.messages.create(\n        model=\"claude-sonnet-4-6\",\n        max_tokens=1024,\n        system=[\n            {\"type\": \"text\", \"text\": \"You are a senior code reviewer.\"},\n            {\n                \"type\": \"text\",\n                \"text\": CODEBASE_CONTENT,\n                \"cache_control\": {\"type\": \"ephemeral\"},  # cache the 150k-token codebase\n            },\n        ],\n        messages=[{\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": f\"Review this PR diff:\\n{pr_diff}\"}],\n    )\n    # First call: ~150k cache_creation_input_tokens (25% price)\n    # Subsequent calls within ~5 min: ~150k cache_read_input_tokens (10% price)\n    return response.content[0].text"
          }
        ]
      },
