            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Treating context length as a substitute for retrieval.",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " Stuffing an entire 1,000-document corpus into a 1M-token context leads to lost-in-the-middle degradation and enormous cost. RAG retrieves the relevant 5 documents — better recall and 99% cheaper."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Not reserving space for the output.",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " The context limit applies to input + output combined. If your input is 199,000 tokens and you set max_tokens=4096, the model has only 1,000 tokens for output and will truncate. Budget for output explicitly."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
